###################################################
# Objective
 Create a web app in python including Google Blockly Editing.
 The output of the Blockly Editer is the Behavior Tree in json formated.

###################################################
# Conditions
## Category
  There is no default category supported by Google Blockly.
  They will be added by 'Generator'
## Folder tree
  CustomBlocks: './static/generated/CustomBlocks'. Block Definition.
  Generators: './static/generated/Generators/'. Code generators
  Toolbox: './static/generated/Toolbox/'. There is a file 'toolboxCustomBasic.js' Json formated Toolbox info.
  Theme: './static/generated/Theme/'. There is a file 'themeForCustomBasic.js' Json formated Theme file for Blocks.

###################################################
# Pages
## Main Page -------------------------------
  - Background: use image file in `./static/assets`.
### Scenario
  - Scnerio List: Show the saved Scnerio list (Behavior Tree)
  - Delete Button: Remove selected Scenario.
  - Create Button: to Create a new Scnerio with the Blockly Editor.
  - Edit Button: to edit a selected Scnerio with the Blockly Editor.
### Block
  - Update Button
    Load and Update the Block List from fixed location file. ./btInfo.
## Edit Page -------------------------------
  - Show the Google Blockly Edit page.
  - If there are blocks or category, show it left side as a normal Blockly app.
  - If there is a selected scenario on the Main Page, show it on the screen.
    The Behavior Tree should be convert to Brockly Json format refer to the json file in btInfo folder.
    Convert only items that has been vound in btInfo.
  - Behavior Tree JSON should not be shown in the right side area.
  - In scenario name input field, pressing `Enter` should save scenario.
    It should behave same as clicking `Save Scenario` button.
## Behavior Tree JSON Window -------------------------------
  - In Edit page, button name is `Behavior Tree` (not `Generate BT JSON`).
  - Clicking `Behavior Tree` opens Graphical Tree window first.
  - Behavior Tree JSON window is opened by `JSON` button in Graphical Tree window.
  - Behavior Tree JSON window has `View Tree` button to go back to Graphical Tree window.
  - When clicking `Generate BT JSON`, open Behavior Tree JSON popup window at center of window.
  - Popup height should be over 70% of window height.
  - Popup card uses main app theme style.
  - JSON text area uses light background color for readability.
  - JSON text should be selectable and copyable to system clipboard.
  - `Confirm` button closes the popup window.
## Graphical Tree Window -------------------------------
  - Window title is `Graphical Tree`.
  - Popup height should be over 70% of window height.
  - Popup width should be over 70% of window width.
  - Show BT tree as graphical nodes and lines.
  - Each tree item color uses the block color of corresponding block.
  - Tree link lines should be horizontal/vertical with rounded corners (not straight diagonal lines).
  - Provide `Zoom In` and `Zoom Out` buttons.
  - Support mouse wheel zoom and drag(pan) interaction.
  - Buttons are centered at bottom.
  - `JSON` button opens Behavior Tree JSON window.
  - `Confirm` button closes Graphical Tree window.
## Top Menu -------------------------------
  Top area shows title text `BRIC Scenario Studio`.
  Clicking `BRIC Scenario Studio` goes back to Main page.
## Notification -------------------------------
  Notification toast message should be shown in the center of the window.
  For scenario Add/Save and Delete actions, include the scenario file name in the message.
  Example messages:
   - Saved: {scenario_name}.json
   - Deleted: {scenario_name}.json

